Hi Team,
VSaaS is now operating normally and successfully scanning images. The errors previously observed were not due to a VSaaS service outage, but rather downstream effects of an ongoing Artifactory federated binary instance performance issue.
Root Cause
The issue is caused by performance degradation in the Artifactory federated instance, impacting the timely synchronization of container images between the main Artifactory and federated instances.
As a result, VSaaS scan requests may intermittently fail when required image artifacts are:
Not yet synchronized, or
Delayed in propagation across federated and main artifactory repositories
Recent Changes
There have been no recent changes on the VSaaS side. The issue is isolated to the Artifactory federated instance and remains under active investigation by the artifactory team.
Current Status
VSaaS: Healthy and functioning as expected
Artifactory Federation: Degraded performance (ongoing)
Impact: Image synchronization delays
Mitigation / Next Steps
The Artifactory team is actively working to stabilize federation performance and reduce synchronization latency
